THE 16 days of activism for no violence against women andchildren did not matter to a KZN man who allegedly stabbed his girlfriend to death.The 44-year-old man from Shayamoya in Shakaskraal, northern KZN allegedly stabbed his girlfriend (37) on Tuesday.The bloody incident took place at the man&rsquo;s house at about 3.30pm.KZN cops spokeswoman Colonel Thembeka Mbhele said the man refused to come out of his house at first but was later arrested by the Umhlali task team.&ldquo;The suspect allegedly stabbed his girlfriend after an argument. &ldquo;Our members received information about the incident and were told the man was armed. They arrived at the scene and gave verbal warnings to the suspect but he did not come out,&rdquo; she said.The cops then sent a patrol dog into the building and the suspect was apprehended.&ldquo;The alleged murder weapon, a knife, was found in his possession. The arrested suspect will appear in the Umhlali periodical court soon,&rdquo; she added.KZN acting provincial commissioner, Major-General Bheki Langa, praised the task team for finding the suspect.